1.Ng5 {%02 (black has 2 moves: Ng5 and fg)} {%03
 (The attacking moves are the best. That's why I recommend you to find the
attacking moves first of all. To make it - you need to focus your attention on
the opponent's territory of the board and think, how can you transfer your
pieces onto such territory and take something or attack something. This simple
idea will help you to find many powerful moves! You should think quickly about
every possible forcing move on the opponent's territory. Most of them will be
very bad, so you will not spend a lot of time.  In this position we should first analyze the moves: Nc8, Nd7, Ne5, Ng5.)}
( 1.Nxc8 Qxc8 {%02 it is already the end of the forcing line. White has an advantage.}
) ( 1.Nxd7 Bxd7 2.Qd3 Be6 {%02 gives nothing for white} )
( 1.Nxe5 Nfxe5 {%02 only helps black to be more active} ) Nxg5
{%02 (Now white has several moves: Nc8, Nd7, Bc4, Bg5. Nc8 and Nd7 removes the
pressure and only helps black. So white should play Bg5 or Bc4)}
( 1...fxg5 {%02 (now white has: Nd7, Nc8, Bg4. But according to the general principles we should keep up a pressure. So Bg4 should be better)}
2.Bg4 {%02 now black cannot do anything really. White will take back the knight on d7 saving a huge advantage in activity}
( 2.Nxc8 Qxc8 3.Bg4 Rd8 {%02 favor black} ) ( 2.Nxd7 Bxd7 3.Bg4
Bxg4 4.Rxd8 Rxd8 {%02 black has a material advantage} ) ) 2.Bxg5
( 2.Bc4+ {%02 is also possible} Nf7 3.Be6 $16 ) fxg5 {%02 (now white has 2 moves: Bc4 and Bg4)}
3.Bc4+ ( 3.Bg4 {%02 provides the same idea, like Bc4-e6, but allows black to play Rf7. So it is a little worse than Bc4}
) Kh8 4.Be6 {%02 then white will take the knight d7 and the black's rook a7 is still out of game}
{As you can see in the hard tactical positions sometimes it is hard to calculate
all the lines. In this case we should use the general principles to realize
which moves should be good, so we will focus the attention mainly onto these moves.}
 1-0

