1.Qe6 {%02 (after this move white is winning in all the lines pretty simply)}
{%03(It is also an example on the topic: finding the moves-candidates. It is very
important TO TURN OFF YOU CRITIQUE on this stage of thinking. You need to think
for a second about EVERY forcing (and attacking) move on the opponent's
territory. One another important rule: in the hard positions (and in the simple
also :) it is easier to focus an attention on every SINGLE piece every time,
starting from queen moves, then rook moves, bishops, knights, pawns. For
example, in this position the first thing you should think about is: "which
forcing moves I can make with the queen on the black's territory". Then you
will find the winning move Qe6. And it will be the FIRST move, which you will
calculate really. While for all other players it will be the LAST move to think about :))}
fxe6 ( 1...Qe8 2.Bxf8 fxe6 ( 2...Nxf8 3.Qxf7+ Qxf7 4.Rxf7 $18 )
3.Bxe6+ Kh8 4.Bg7# ) ( 1...Nf6 2.Nxf6+ Bxf6 3.Qxf6 $18 ) 2.Bxe6+
Rf7 3.Bxf7+ Kh8 4.Bg7# 1-0

